ons ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 13.847485, "shard": "07", "shelf_id": "sn86092219, 1924-02-07, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/wvu", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["west virginia", "richwood", "united states", "nicholas"], "subject_headings": ["United States--West Virginia--Nicholas--Richwood"], "subjects": [{"nicholas": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:nicholas&fo=json"}, {"richwood": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:richwood&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}, {"west virginia": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:west+virginia&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2025-07-17T07:52:34.245Z", "title": "The Nicholas republican (Richwood, W. Va.), February 7, 1924", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn86092219/1924-02-07/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86092219/"], "batch": ["wvu_monroe_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1903", "description": ["Weekly Began in 1903. Cf. Brown, William G. Hist. of Nicholas Co., W. Va. -v. 60, no. 50 (Dec. 19, 1963). Established by W.G. Brown, S.C. Dotson & Logan S. Dotson with John A. Grose as a silent partner and was printed on the press of: Nicholas Chronicle in Summersville, W. Va. Editor: S.